8.9 Platform Permissions & App Store Compliance
🚨  Failure to implement these requirements will result in App Store rejection. These are not optional.
8.9.1 iOS Requirements
•	Microphone: NSMicrophoneUsageDescription in Info.plist — 'SoulSeer uses your microphone for live voice and video readings with spiritual readers.'
•	Camera: NSCameraUsageDescription — 'SoulSeer uses your camera for live video readings with spiritual readers.'
•	Background audio: UIBackgroundModes = ['audio'] in Info.plist. AVAudioSession category: .playAndRecord, mode: .voiceChat.
•	Background video: video transmission pauses when app goes to background — audio continues. Video resumes on foreground return.
•	In-app purchases: the 'Add Funds' balance top-up must be carefully reviewed against App Store guideline 3.1.1 before launch — if it flows through Apple Pay natively, Apple takes 30%.
8.9.2 Android Requirements
•	RECORD_AUDIO and CAMERA in AndroidManifest.xml — runtime permission requests required
•	Foreground service required to keep audio session alive in background — must show a persistent notification: 'SoulSeer reading in progress — X minutes elapsed.'
8.9.3 Permission Denied Handling
•	If microphone denied: show explanation screen with button to open device Settings — do not crash
•	If camera denied: allow voice and chat readings to proceed — only block video readings
•	Never request permissions at app launch — only when the user is about to join a session

8.10 Error Handling — Every Failure Mode
Failure	When It Happens	Required Handling
Token fetch fails	Network error calling agora-token endpoint	Retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff. If all fail, show error and return to dashboard.
Agora join fails	Invalid token, network timeout, channel error	Show user-friendly message with Agora error code in logs. Offer retry.
Billing tick DB error	DB connection lost during charging	Log error. Do not notify user. Retry next tick. If 3 consecutive failures, end session safely.
Reader drops mid-session	Reader loses connection	Start grace period. Notify client. Client UI shows reconnecting state.
Client drops mid-session	Client loses connection	Start grace period. Notify reader.
Server restart mid-session	Deployment or crash	On restart, query for in_progress readings, charge elapsed minutes, mark completed.
Agora token expires mid-session	Session exceeds 1 hour	Client silently calls token refresh endpoint. Renew without interrupting the session.


8.11 Testing Requirements Before Launch
🚨  The reading system cannot be launched without passing every test scenario listed here. A billing bug in production is a financial and reputational emergency.
8.11.1 Billing Accuracy Tests
•	Run a chat session for exactly 3 minutes. Verify client charged exactly 3x pricePerMinute. Verify reader received exactly 3x Math.floor(pricePerMinute * 0.70).
•	Start a session. Kill the client app after 2 minutes. Rejoin within grace period. Continue 1 more minute. End. Verify total billed = 3 minutes, grace period not charged.
•	Start a session with client balance equal to exactly 2 minutes' worth. Verify low balance warning fires. Let balance exhaust. Verify session ends automatically and client is not overdrawn.
•	Call POST /api/readings/:id/start twice rapidly. Verify only one billing timer starts and client is not double-charged.
•	Call POST /api/readings/:id/end twice rapidly. Verify reading is only finalized once.
8.11.2 Connection Tests
•	Start a voice reading. Put client phone in airplane mode for 90 seconds (within grace period). Restore. Verify session resumes and billing continues correctly.
•	Start a voice reading. Put client phone in airplane mode for 3 minutes (past grace period). Verify session finalized for billed minutes only.
•	Start a video reading. Background the app. Verify audio continues and video pauses. Foreground the app. Verify video resumes.
8.11.3 Platform Tests
•	Test all three reading types (chat, voice, video) on a physical iOS device
•	Test all three reading types on a physical Android device
•	Test all three reading types in a desktop web browser (Chrome, Safari)
•	Test the Add Funds flow end-to-end with a real Stripe test card
•	Test the full reading lifecycle with real Agora credentials in a staging environment — never launch using demo credentials
•	Test with two physical devices in the same room to verify audio/video quality and latency

8.12 Post-Session Features
8.12.1 Chat Transcript
•	Chat transcripts stored in the readings table as a jsonb array of { senderId, senderName, content, timestamp } objects
•	Built during the session by the POST /api/readings/:id/message endpoint — every message appended
