18. Client–Reader Direct Messaging
Outside of live reading sessions, clients can send direct messages to any reader on the platform at no cost. The reader then decides — per reply — whether their response is free or paid. If the reader marks a response as paid, the client must approve and pay that price before the message is revealed.
⚠️  This is an outside-of-session feature only. It is completely separate from the Agora RTM chat that occurs during a live reading session. Do not conflate the two systems.
18.1 How It Works — User Flow
Client Sends a Message
•	Client navigates to any reader profile page and clicks 'Send Message', or accesses the Messages section in their dashboard
•	Client can message any reader regardless of whether that reader is online
•	Sending a message is always free for the client
•	Client types their message (plain text, max 2000 characters) and submits
•	Message is delivered to the reader's message inbox
Reader Receives and Replies
•	Reader sees the incoming message in their dashboard inbox with client's display name and message content
•	Reader composes their reply and before sending chooses one of two options:
◦	Send as Free — reply is delivered immediately at no charge to the client
◦	Send as Paid — reader sets a price for this specific reply (minimum $1, maximum $500, whole dollars only)
•	Paid reply content is stored server-side but not revealed to the client until payment is made
Client Receives a Paid Reply
•	Client sees in the thread: 'Reader Name has sent you a paid message — $X.XX to unlock'
•	Client sees the price but NOT the content until they pay
•	Client clicks 'Unlock Message' — system checks their account balance
•	If sufficient balance: amount deducted from client's accountBalance and reply is immediately revealed
•	If insufficient balance: client is shown a prompt to add funds before they can unlock
•	Client cannot be charged without explicitly clicking 'Unlock Message' — no auto-charges
18.2 Reader Controls & Settings
•	Readers can set a default reply type preference in their dashboard: 'Always Free' or 'Always Paid with default price' — pre-fills the reply form but can be overridden per message
•	Readers can set a default paid reply price that pre-populates when they choose paid
•	Readers can view which of their paid replies have been unlocked vs. still pending payment
18.3 Revenue Split for Paid Replies
•	Same 70/30 split as readings: reader receives 70% of the paid reply price, platform retains 30%
•	Example: reader sets $10 paid reply — client pays $10, reader earns $7, platform earns $3
•	Reader's 70% credited to their accountBalance immediately upon client unlocking
•	Transaction logged in the transactions table with type 'paid_message'
⚠️  All balance operations for paid messages must use DB transactions — deduct from client and credit reader atomically, never in separate queries.
18.4 Database Schema
Field	Type	Notes
id	integer PK	Auto-increment
senderId	integer FK	References users — message author
receiverId	integer FK	References users — message recipient
content	text	Message body — always stored in full
isPaid	boolean	False = free. True = paid reply.
price	integer	Null if free. Price in cents if paid.
readerAmount	integer	Null if free. Reader's 70% cut in cents.
platformAmount	integer	Null if free. Platform's 30% cut in cents.
isUnlocked	boolean	False = paid and not yet paid for. True = free or paid and unlocked.
unlockedAt	timestamp	Null until client pays.
createdAt	timestamp	When message was sent
readAt	timestamp	Null until recipient views it

🚨  Content is always stored in plain text server-side. The paid gate is enforced at the API level — the content field is stripped from the response until isUnlocked = true. Never rely on the client to hide content.
18.5 Critical API Behavior Rules
•	GET /api/messages/:userId — strip the content field from any row where isPaid = true AND isUnlocked = false. Replace with '[Paid message — $X.XX to unlock]'
•	POST /api/messages/:userId/reply — only readers can call this. Validate price is between 100 and 50000 cents. Calculate and store readerAmount and platformAmount at write time, not at unlock time.
•	POST /api/messages/:id/unlock — verify requesting user is the message's receiverId. Verify isPaid = true and isUnlocked = false (prevent double-unlock). Check balance. Deduct and credit atomically in a DB transaction. Set isUnlocked = true and unlockedAt = now(). Return full message content in the response.
•	Rate limit: POST /api/messages/:userId — 20 messages per 5 minutes per user to prevent spam
18.6 UI Requirements
Messages Dashboard Section (both roles)
•	Conversation list: sorted by most recent message, shows other party's name and profile photo, preview of last message, unread count badge, timestamp
•	Unread message count displayed as a badge on the Messages nav link
Thread View
•	Messages displayed chronologically, oldest at top, newest at bottom
•	Client messages on the right, reader messages on the left — standard chat layout
•	Paid locked messages display as a blurred/greyed card with price and 'Unlock Message — $X.XX' button
•	Paid unlocked messages display normally with a subtle 'Paid' label
Reader Reply Composer
•	Reply input plus a toggle: 'Free Reply' / 'Paid Reply'
•	Selecting 'Paid Reply' reveals a price input — pre-filled with default paid reply price from settings
•	Price input: whole dollars only. Minimum $1, maximum $500.
•	Clear label before sending: 'Client will be charged $X.XX to read this reply'
Unlock Flow (Client)
•	If sufficient balance: single confirmation tap — 'Unlock for $X.XX from your balance' — message reveals inline without page reload
•	If insufficient balance: open the Add Funds flow with required amount pre-filled, return to thread after funding
•	Unlocked message reveals with a smooth animation — not a jarring page refresh
18.7 Security
•	Paid message content must NEVER appear in any API response to the client until isUnlocked = true — enforce at the query/serialization layer
•	Only the message's receiverId can unlock a paid message — never allow a third party to unlock
•	Only a reader can send a paid reply — clients cannot send paid messages
•	Prevent double-unlock: check isUnlocked = false before processing payment in a DB transaction

